'''Bart Verbruggen''' (born 18 August 2002) is a Dutch professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a goalkeeper for {{English football updater|Brigh&HA}} club [[Brighton & Hove Albion F.C.|Brighton & Hove Albion]] and the [[Netherlands national football team|Netherlands national team]].

==Club career==
===Anderlecht===
Verbruggen joined [[R.S.C. Anderlecht|Anderlecht]] in 2020 from [[N.A.C. Breda]]. He made his professional debut on 2 May 2021, in a 2–2 [[Belgian First Division A]] draw against [[Club Brugge]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://uk.soccerway.com/matches/2021/05/02/belgium/pro-league/club-brugge-kv/royal-sporting-club-anderlecht/3496939/|title=Club Brugge vs. Anderlecht |date=24 October 2021|publisher=Soccerway}}</ref> On 23 February 2023, he saved all three penalties during a shootout against [[PFC Ludogorets Razgrad|Ludogorets Razgrad]] in the [[2022–23 UEFA Europa Conference League]] knockout round play-offs second leg, which helped his team to win the tie 3–0 on penalties following a 2–2 draw on aggregate.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefaconferenceleague/video/027e-1763da99f9d2-d77cd1537c85-1000--uecl-laufenn-potw-spieler-st8-bart-verbruggen-anderlecht-v-/ |title=UECL – Laufenn – POTW Spieler – ST8 – Bart Verbruggen (Anderlecht v Ludogorets) |publisher=UEFA |date=24 February 2023 }}</ref>

===Brighton & Hove Albion===
On 3 July 2023, [[Brighton & Hove Albion F.C.|Brighton & Hove Albion]] announced the signing of Verbruggen on a five-year deal.<ref>{{cite web |url = https://www.brightonandhovealbion.com/news/3565404/albion-sign-bart-verbruggen-from-anderlecht |title = Albion sign Bart Verbruggen from Anderlecht |website = Brighton & Hove Albion F.C. |date = 3 July 2023 |accessdate = 3 July 2023}}</ref> Verbruggen was chosen to play ahead of [[Jason Steele (footballer)|Jason Steele]] to make his debut in Brighton's third match of [[2023–24 Brighton & Hove Albion F.C. season|the season]] on 26 August, a 3–1 home loss against [[West Ham United F.C.|West Ham United]] for their first defeat of the season.<ref>{{cite web|url = https://www.brightonandhovealbion.com/news/3653728/record-for-gross-but-albion-are-beaten|title = Record for Gross but Albion are beaten|website = Brighton & Hove Albion F.C.|date = 26 August 2023|accessdate = 26 August 2023|archive-date = 26 August 2023|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20230826185239/https://www.brightonandhovealbion.com/news/3653728/record-for-gross-but-albion-are-beaten|url-status = dead}}</ref>

On 18 February 2024, Verbruggen would keep his first Premier League clean-sheet in a 5–0 win against [[Sheffield United F.C|Sheffield United]].

Verbruggen made his first [[Premier League]] start of Brighton's [[2024–25 Brighton & Hove Albion F.C. season|2024–25 campaign]] on 31 August 2024 in Albion's 1–1 draw against [[Arsenal F.C.|Arsenal]] after missing their opening two games due to injury.<ref name="Soccerway">{{Cite web |title=Netherlands – B. Verbruggen – Profile with news, career statistics and history – Soccerway |url=https://ie.soccerway.com/players/bart-verbruggen/622387/matches/ |access-date=2024-09-02 |publisher=Soccerway}}</ref>

== International career ==
On 17 March 2023, Verbruggen received his first official call-up to the [[Netherlands national football team|Dutch senior national team]] for the [[UEFA Euro 2024 qualifying|UEFA Euro 2024 qualifiers]] against [[France national football team|France]] and [[Gibraltar national football team|Gibraltar]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=17 March 2023 |title=Koeman roept drie debutanten op |url=https://www.onsoranje.nl/nieuws/nederlands-elftal/80692/koeman-roept-drie-debutanten-op |access-date=17 March 2023 |website=Royal Dutch Football Association |language=nl-NL}}</ref> He made a debut in the national team on 13 October 2023 in a 1–2 loss against France.<ref>{{cite web |title=Frankrijk doet Oranje ook in Amsterdam pijn: 1–2 |url=https://www.onsoranje.nl/nieuws/nederlands-elftal-mannen/81065/frankrijk-doet-oranje-ook-amsterdam-pijn-1-2 |website=onsoranje.nl |publisher=[[Royal Dutch Football Association]] |access-date=14 October 2023 |language=nl |date=13 October 2023}}</ref>

On 29 May 2024, Verbruggen was named in the Netherlands' squad for [[UEFA Euro 2024]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/5526712/2024/05/29/netherlands-euro-2024-squad-confirmed/|title=Example Title|date=29 May 2024|access-date=7 June 2024|website=The New York Times}}</ref> He went on to play in each of the Netherlands' matches in the tournament, reaching the semi-finals.<ref name="Soccerway"/>

